<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Rescue911     09-21 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Rescue 911,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>TV Crime Show's Film Crew Gets Taste of Real Thing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A crew from CBS-TV's ``Rescue 911'' that
came to Fort Worth to film a burglary re-enactment got a first-hand
look at real crime.
   A $30,000 camera disappeared Monday night as the crew was
unloading equipment to shoot a segment about real-life emergencies.
   ``It's a sad fact for Fort Worth,'' said police Lt. Alvin Allcon.
``Here someone is filming a property crime and then they become a
victim of a property crime.''
   Investigators believe a passer-by simply walked away with the
camera that was left unattended on a sidewalk. They have no leads.
   Filming resumed Monday night after the crew got another camera.
</TEXT>
