<FILEID>AP-NR-09-21-89 0119EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-AircraftExplosion     09-21 0151</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Aircraft Explosion,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>Aircraft Explodes at Eielson AFB</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Alaska Air National Guard tanker
aircraft exploded and burned Wednesday at Eielson Air Force Base,
killing two people, Air Force officials said.
   Five people aboard the KC-135 tanker were treated for minor
injuries, along with two base firefighters, said Sgt. Gene LaDoucer.
The aircraft was destroyed.
   The plane apparently was taxiing to park when the explosion
occurred at about 3 p.m. LaDoucer said the Eielson public affairs
office was notified at 5 p.m. that the fire was out.
   Five of the seven people aboard were crew members, and the other
two were military passengers, he said. Names were withheld until
relatives could be notified.
   LaDoucer said an Air Force board will investigate the cause of
the crash and probably will release findings in several months.
   The aircraft was part of the 168th Air Refueling Squadron at
Eielson.
</TEXT>
