<FIRST>r a PM-AircraftExplosion     09-21 0176</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Aircraft Explosion,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>Aircraft Explodes at Base; Two Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Alaska Air National Guard tanker
aircraft exploded and burned at Eielson Air Force Base, killing two
people, the Air Force said. The five others aboard received minor
injuries.
   Sgt. Gene LaDoucer said the KC-135 plane apparently was taxiing
to park when the explosion occurred at about 3 p.m. Wednesday. The
fire, which destroyed the plane, was reported out within two hours.
   Two base firefighters also were treated for minor injuries,
officials said.
   The cause of the explosion was not immediately known. An Air
Force board will investigate the incident, LaDoucer said.
   Five of the seven people aboard were crew members, and the two
others were military passengers, LaDoucer said. Names were withheld.
   The plane, used for in-flight refueling, was returning from a
routine training mission, Sgt. Walt Johnson said. He said he did not
know how much fuel was aboard.
   The Boeing-built aircraft, 134 feet long and with a windowless
fuselage, was part of the 168th Air Refueling Squadron at Eielson.
</TEXT>
