<FILEID>AP-NR-09-21-89 2027EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-BusCrash-List     09-21 0443</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bus Crash-List,0458</SECOND>
<HEAD>List Of Recent Domestic Bus Disasters</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Bus Crash Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of some other fatal bus accidents:
   May 14, 1988 _ Church-owned school bus bursts into flames after
colliding with pickup truck being driven by drunk driver on wrong
side of Interstate 71 near Carrollton, Ky. Three adults and 24
children are killed.
   Oct. 20, 1987 _ Tractor-trailer crashes into disabled college bus
near Gaffney, S.C, killing four people and injuring 13.
   Aug. 28, 1987 _ Truck slams into school bus carrying handicapped
children near Bronson, Fla., killing six and injuring 17.
   July 17, 1987 _ Raging floodwaters of the Guadalupe River in
Texas carry away bus and van carrying 43 people, killing 10
teen-agers from a church camp.
   May 30, 1986 _ Speeding Starline Sightseeing Tours coach wrecks
in California canyon, killing 21 passengers. The driver was
sentenced to four years in prison.
   May 31, 1985 _ Truck crosses center line and slams into school
bus near Snow Hill, N.C., killing five children and injuring 20.
   Jan. 21, 1984 _ High school wrestling team's bus collides with
tanker truck near West Glacier, Mont., killing nine people aboard
and injuring 19.
   March 25, 1983 _ Bus carrying school children to a state
convention leaves rural road near Uno, Ark., and overturns, killing
four students and five teachers.
   Dec. 24, 1983 _ Bus carrying worshipers to Christmas revival
collides with truck near Devers, Texas, killing nine people and
injuring 14.
   Nov. 30, 1983 _ Continental Trailways bus rams rear of truck near
Livingston, Texas and plunges 40 feet into a creek, killing six
passengers and injuring the driver and five others.
   April 5, 1983 _ Tractor-trailer involved in accident with bus
carrying mentally retarded and handicapped adults near New Berlin,
N.Y. Five passengers killed and 16 others injured.
   Feb. 18, 1981 _ Commuter bus crashes through guardrail near
Quantico, Va., and plunges down 80-foot embankment into creek,
killing 11 people and injuring 13.
   June 5, 1980 _ Tour bus carrying mostly senior citizens from
Dallas to Branson, Mo., plunges into 40-foot ravine near Jasper,
Ark., killing 20 people and injuring 13.
   May 21, 1976 _ School bus carrying 53 Yuba City, Calif., High
School students plunges off freeway ramp near Martinez. Twenty-eight
students and a teacher are killed.
   Sept. 17, 1963 _ In what is believed to be the worst bus accident
in U.S. history, bus collides with a train near Salinas, Calif.,
killing 32 farm workers.
   Feb. 28, 1958 _ School bus from Prestonsburg, Ky., plunges into
the Levisa Fork of the Big Sandy River, killing 26 students and the
bus driver.
</TEXT>
