<FIRST>r a AM-BedfordSprings     09-21 0324</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bedford Springs,0331</SECOND>
<HEAD>No Sale for Historic Spa</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Hobert cq in 2nd graf.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CATHERINE DRESSLER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEDFORD SPRINGS, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The historic Bedford Springs Hotel
went on the auction block Thursday, but its owners rejected the high
bid of $5.3 million as not enough for the 185-year-old building and
2,300 acres of mountain land.
   ``I think the vultures were here looking to scoop up a bargain,''
said Hobert Hobbs, vice president of Sky Group International Inc.,
which owns the resort. ``We've been in a lot of battles. We're not
going to give up the war.''
   About 200 people crowded into the lobby of the Bedford County
hotel, but neither the owner nor auctioneer David Fox would say how
many bids were offered during the hourlong auction. Neither
identified the high bidder.
   The auction was held nine days before $4.8 million is due to
Union National Bank of Pittsburgh. The money was spent out of a $7.5
million loan made in 1987 for renovations never completed because of
a dispute between owners that ended up in federal bankruptcy court.
   Hobbs would not say how much Sky Group International wants for
the 244-room hotel and surrounding land, which includes a golf
course and wooded trails. As for the bidding, he said, ``It was
considerably far off.''
   He said the owners would continue to seek new financing to pay
Union National Bank before it forecloses on the property.
   Hobbs said the high bid would not have covered second mortgages
on the property and unsecured debt.
   ``We'd rather take our chances that in nine more days we can find
the financing,'' Hobbs said. ``We're going to continue and say a lot
of prayers.''
   The hotel is a stately stretch of three- and four-story buildings
in the Allegheny Mountains. In its glory days, it attracted notables
including six presidents, but now all but 66 of its 244 rooms have
been closed to guests.
