<HEAD>Eds: Members who used f0291, AM-Farm Outlook transmitted Wednesday
under a Washington dateline, are asked to use the following story.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press erroneously reported Sept.
20 that the number of farms declined by 266,600 per year during the
1980s.
   The 266,600 figure represents the total decline in the number of
farms over the decade.
