<FIRST>r f BC-AutoProduction     09-21 0150</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Production,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Up-Down This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
233,221 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
211,051, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in
which 235,068 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 154,387 cars this week,
compared with 141,423 a week ago and 147,496 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 78,834,
compared with last week's 69,628 and last year's 87,572.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,488 cars this week, up from
19,661 a week ago and down from last year's 20,719.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 20,920, compared
with 20,566 a week ago and 21,831 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
