<FIRST>r f BC-KnightRidder-Moves     09-21 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Knight Ridder-Moves,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Newspaper Chain Promotes Two Senior Executives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Knight-Ridder Inc., the newspaper publishing and
communications company, on Thursday announced the promotion of two
senior executives.
   W.H. ``Gus'' Harwell was promoted from group vice president for
operations to senior vice president for operations. Jay Harris,
assistant to the president of Knight-Ridder, gained the additional
post of vice president for operations.
   Harwell, 59, who was publisher of the Tallahassee Democrat and
the Boca Raton News before becoming a corporate officer, will
oversee operations of 14 newspapers from Long Beach, Calif., to
Myrtle Beach, S.C., in his new role.
   Harris, 40, joined Knight-Ridder in 1985 as executive editor of
the Philadelphia Daily News after serving as assistant dean of
Northwestern University's Medill School of Journalism. He will
oversee six newspapers, the company said in a statement.
   Among its 28 newspapers, Knight-Ridder publishes The Miami
Herald, The Philadelphia Inquirer, the Detroit Free Press and the
San Jose Mercury News.
