   That came as a mild surprise to analysts, who had generally been
expecting no change in the GNP reading from the 2.7 percent
estimated increase the department reported last month.
   The resulting suggestion of a slower-than-expected pace of
business activity helped stocks gain ground in early trading.
   But after the advance faltered near the 2,700 level in the Dow
Jones industrial average, prices began to retreat.
   Brokers said much of the late pressure on the market came from
traders engaged in computer-program strategies involving stock index
options and futures and the prominent stocks that are components of
the indexes.
   Chase Manhattan climbed { to 40 in active trading. Wall Streeters
generally upgraded their appraisals of the company's earnings
